nited States. As of 2014, the world's largest exporter of edible ___s is Indonesia. In Brazil, Mexico and the Caribbean, many ___s are still caught wild.","wiki"),("wolf","4","In the sixth century BC, the first ___ bounty was reportedly opened when Solon of Athens offered five silver drachmas to any hunter for killing any male ___, and one for every female.","wiki"),("carp","4","Most cypriniformes have scales and teeth on the inferior pharyngeal bones which may be modified in relation to the diet. Tribolodon is the only cyprinid genus which tolerates salt water. Several species move into brackish water but return to fresh water to spawn. All of the other cypriniformes live in continental waters and have a wide geographical range., and the family Cyprinidae itself is often known as the ___ family.","wiki"),("pike","4","The species of this genus are known as ___ and pickerel. The type species is E. lucius, the northern ___.","wiki"),("swai","4","The meat is often marketed under the common name ___. It has also been introduced into other river basins as a food source, and its striking appearance and iridescence have made it popular with fishkeeping hobbyists, among whom it is also known as the Siamese shark or sutchi catfish. The ___'s omnivorous diet consists of crustaceans, other fish, and plant matter.","wiki"),("tuna","4","A ___ , and is believed to live up to 50 years.","wiki"),("crab","4","___ meat or ___meat is the meat found within a ___. It is used in many cuisines across the world, prized for its soft, delicate and sweet taste. ___ meat is low in fat and contains around 340 kJ  are among the most commercially available species of ___meat globally.","wiki"),("aged","4","In the 1960s, the cheaper wet-aging process largely displaced dry aging as the meat is 15–25% more expensive than wet-___ beef: dry hanging rooms are expensive; meat weight is reduced through evaporation; and some proportion of meat spoils.","wiki"),("chop","4","A meat ___ is a cut of meat cut 