m the combinations of the word uppu, meaning salt In North India, the dish is called ___. In Maharashtra the dish traditionally had the name saanja in Marathi.","wiki"),("pohe","4","This easily digestible form of raw rice is very popular across India, Nepal and Bangladesh, and is normally used to prepare snacks or light and easy fast food in a variety of Indian cuisine styles, some even for long-term consumption of a week or more. It is known by a variety of names: avalakki  in Konkani.","wiki"),("kuih","4","___  are bite-sized snack or dessert foods commonly found in Southeast Asia. It is a fairly broad term which may include items that would be called cakes, cookies, dumplings, pudding, biscuits, or pastries in English and are usually made from rice or glutinous rice. The term kueh or ___ is widely used in Indonesia, Malaysia, Brunei, and Singapore, to refer to sweet or savoury desserts. Though called by other names, one is likely to find various similar versions of ___ in neighbouring countries, such as Vietnam, Thailand, and Myanmar. For example, the colourful steamed kue lapis and the rich ___ bingka ubi are also available in Myanmar, Thailand, and Vietnam. In the Philippines, ___ are referred to in Tagalog as kakanin.","wiki"),("puto","4","The most common shape of the putuhán steamer used in making ___ is round, ranging from 30 to 60 centimetres . The cover is almost always conical to allow the condensing steam to drip along the perimeter instead of on the cakes.","wiki"),("tuak","4","Bowl for ___ drinking made from a gourd ","wiki"),("acar","4","___ is a type of vegetable pickle from Indonesia","wiki"),("kaya","4","Coconut jam , Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore and Thailand.","wiki"),("jeok","4","___  and wedding ceremonies. ___ comes in multiple varieties, including san___ and nureum-___.","wiki"),("list","4","This is a ___ of notable barbecue restaurants. Barbecue is a method and apparatus for char grilling food in the hot smoke of a wood fire, usually 